Look for a child view that matches the specified predicate, starting with the specified view and its descendents and then recusively searching the ancestors and siblings of that view until this view is reached. This method is useful in cases where the predicate does not match a single unique view (perhaps multiple views use the same id) and we are trying to find the view that is "closest" in scope to the starting view. Params: start – The view to start from. predicate – The predicate to evaluate. Returns: The first view that matches the predicate or null.
